ngland, United Kingdom","Barnham, Suffolk, England":"Barnham, Suffolk, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Astley","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of several places in England called Astley (in Lancashire, Shropshire, Warwickshire, Worcestershire, and Yorkshire), from Old English <i>ēast</i> ‘east’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’. The modern surname seems to be particularly associated with the one in Warwickshire. See also   Astle  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Astle","meanings":["English: habitational name from a place in Cheshire called Astle, from Old English <i>ēast</i> ‘east’ + <i>hyll</i> ‘hill’. There may also have been some confusion with <i>Asthall</i> and   Astley  . Or occasionally this may be a topographic name denoting residence on an ‘east hill’ (from Middle English <i>ast</i> + <i>hill</i> or <i>hull</i>), i.e. a hill to the east of a settlement.","English: perhaps also a habitational name from Astwell, Northamptonshire, from Old English <i>ēast</i> ‘east’ + <i>wielle</i> ‘spring’.","English: habitational name from Asthall, Oxfordshire, from Old English <i>ēast</i> ‘east’ + <i>halh</i> ‘nook’."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":20,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Astley was born in 1435, in Melton, Suffolk, England. She had at least 1 daughter with James de Calthorpe. She died in 1503, in Blakeney, Norfolk, England, at the age of 68."},"et":{"1435–1503":"1435–1503","1420–1476":"1420–1476","1446–1498":"1446–1498","1503":"1503","1435":"1435","1446":"1446","1455":"1455","1476":"1476","1498":"1498","1420":"1420","Blakeney, Norfolk, England":"Blakeney, Norfolk, England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Melton, Suffolk, England":"Melton, Suffolk, England","Isleham Manor, Cambridgeshire, England":"Isleham, Cambridgeshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Barnham, Suffolk, England":"Barnham, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"1435–1503":"1435–1503","1420–1476":"1420–1476","1446–1498":"1446–1498","1503":"1503","1435":"1435","1446":"1446","1455":"1455","1476":"1476","1498":"1498","1420":"1420","Blakeney, Norfolk, England":"Blakeney, Norfolk, England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Melton, Suffolk, England":"Melton, Suffolk, England","Isleham Manor, Cambridgeshire, England":"Isleham, Cambridgeshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Barnham, Suffolk, England":"Barnham, Suffolk, England"},"fr":{"1435–1503":"1435–1503","1420–1476":"1420–1476","1446–1498":"1446–1498","1503":"1503","1435":"1435","1446":"1446","1455":"1455","1476":"1476","1498":"1498","1420":"1420","Blakeney, Norfolk, England"